		<text oae-label="Text" oae-type="textarea" oae-rows="15">
			<![CDATA[<b>A:</b>	I'm excited about <blank word="repainting"/>(<i>repaint</i>) the living room.
<b>B:</b>	Me too.  I'm sick and tired of <blank word="looking"/> (<i>look</i>) at the same boring color for so many years.
<b>A:</b>	I want <blank word="to pick"/> (<i>pick</i>) a bright color.  Maybe yellow?
<b>B:</b>	I don't mind <blank word="choosing"/> (<i>choose</i>) a bright color, but yellow is out of the question.  How about green?
<b>A:</b>	Well, the kitchen is green. Our bedroom is green.  Even the bathroom is green. I don't feel like <blank word="painting"/> (<i>paint</i>) anything else green.
<b>B:</b>	OK.  We need <blank word="to look"/> (<i>look</i>) at these color samples.  Hey, how about <blank word="painting"/> (<i>paint</i>) the living room blue?
<b>A:</b>	Hmm.  Let's see.  I don't object to <blank word="using"/> (<i>use</i>) blue.  But I would really like <blank word="to use"/> (<i>use</i>) this light blue.  I think it's more cheerful than the dark blue.
<b>B:</b>	I like the light blue, too! 
<b>A:</b>	Now we just need <blank word="to decide"/>(<i>decide</i>) what colors to repaint the kitchen, bedroom, and bathroom!]]>
		</text>
